<subSubSection id="7B05903129A001F74F07203C79A31A90" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9603F3357F3F366215EC197E7D752E5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7562DFB4F9247550D7B941A4FBA1017F" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="72AE574E7895B826DD92604EC1816837" authorityName="J. Calvo" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Xenophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xenophyllum funkianum" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="funkianum">
<emphasis id="FA867138AE78171ADD93A920289AC775" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Xenophyllum funkianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well characterized by its creeping rhizome-like stems 20-35 cm long, the straight linear leaves prolonged into a sheath-like base that bears arachnoid trichomes, the dark-burgundy sessile involucres with 13-14 involucral bracts, the 12-13 white ray florets somewhat purplish beneath, and by having white-villous achenes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
